    "body": "`ls` is also an alias in IPython, you can redefine it interactively to just `ls` with\r\n\r\n```\r\nIn [1]: alias ls ls\r\n```\r\n\r\nuse `hist -t ` to see the equivalent Python code:\r\n```\r\nIn [2]: hist -t\r\nget_ipython().run_line_magic('alias', 'ls ls')\r\nget_ipython().run_line_magic('hist', '-t')\r\n```\r\n\r\nPlace the equivalent code into `~/.ipython/profile_default/startup/alias.py` (choose the nname you like) with any other logic you like, like looking at the `$TERM` env or `infocmp` to know whether color is supported or not.\r\n\r\nDoes that fits your need ? \r\n\r\nIf so feel free to close the issue.\r\n"
  },
