    "body": "> Do you think this an acceptable solution? If yes I can submit the pull request.\r\n\r\nYes, that sounds good. \r\n\r\n> I don't quite understand what is a `Configurable` and what does `List(default_aliases()).tag(config=True)` imply. Why should the `default_aliases` be a class data member instead of instance data member?\r\n\r\nDon't worry about that, it's the metaclass magic that  allow `c.AliasManger.default_aliases.append(...)/.prepend(...)` to work in the configuration file, and `--AliasManger.default_aliases=...` to work similarly as a command line argument. \r\n\r\nYou  can tread `default_aliases` as a instance attribute which is of type list for all purposes."
